data.content:
Here's what changed and how to fix each issue. **`Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi` 10.0 uses OpenAPI.NET v2**, which has several breaking changes:

---

### 1. `OpenApiString` removed → use `JsonNode`
All `OpenApiAny` types (`OpenApiString`, `OpenApiFloat`, etc.) are gone. `Schema.Example` is now `JsonNode` with implicit conversions:

```diff
- using Microsoft.OpenApi.Any;
+ using System.Text.Json.Nodes;
+ using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models.References;

- param.Schema.Example = new OpenApiString("1.0");
+ param.Schema.Example = "1.0";  // implicit JsonNode conversion
```

### 2. `Nullable` removed → use `JsonSchemaType` flags
OpenAPI 3.1 uses type arrays instead of `nullable`. The `Type` property is now a `[Flags] enum JsonSchemaType`:

```diff
- property.Value.Nullable = false;
+ if (property.Value.Type.HasValue)
+     property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
```

To **make** something nullable, you'd do `Type |= JsonSchemaType.Null`.

### 3. `Reference` property removed from models → use `*Reference` types
`OpenApiSecurityScheme.Reference` no longer exists. Use `OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference`:

```diff
- var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecurityScheme
- {
-     Reference = new OpenApiReference { Type = ReferenceType.SecurityScheme, Id = "oauth2" }
- };
+ var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2", context.Document);
```

(`context.Document` was added to operation/schema transformer contexts in .NET 10.)

### 4. Collections may be `null` by default
In v2, collections are **not** pre-initialized. Guard with `??=`:

```diff
+ operation.Responses ??= new OpenApiResponses();
  operation.Responses.TryAdd("401", new OpenApiResponse { Description = "Unauthorized" });

+ operation.Security ??= [];
```

---

### Full corrected code

```csharp
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models.References;

options.AddOperationTransformer((operation, context, ct) =>
{
    var param = operation.Parameters?.FirstOrDefault(p => p.Name == "api-version");
    if (param is not null)
    {
        param.Schema.Example = "1.0";  // implicit JsonNode
    }

    operation.Responses ??= new OpenApiResponses();
    operation.Responses.TryAdd("401", new OpenApiResponse { Description = "Unauthorized" });

    var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2", context.Document);
    operation.Security ??= [];
    operation.Security.Add(new OpenApiSecurityRequirement
    {
        [oAuthScheme] = scopes
    });

    return Task.CompletedTask;
});

options.AddSchemaTransformer((schema, context, ct) =>
{
    if (schema.Properties is not null)
    {
        foreach (var property in schema.Properties)
        {
            if (schema.Required?.Contains(property.Key) != true
                && property.Value.Type.HasValue)
            {
                property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
            }
        }
    }
    return Task.CompletedTask;
});
```

**Summary of key changes:**
